) refused to respect that request, which they're perfectly allowed to do, it just means they're not acting in an amicable way. I haven't been either, but only because I've been forced to do some comment moderation, which I don't feel good about.

As I explained a moment ago, I had to delete one of his comments because it included a kind of subversive sexism that I will not allow in this community. As far as I can tell, he meant no harm, but that's irrelevant.

This stuff is hard, but I'm doing my best. I have learned a lot from this experience. I don't like how I've handled things generally. However, sexism is not allowed and I feel I was correct to remove it. But I never said that Vladimir was unwelcome, and I've spent a considerable amount of time trying to show him that he is, and help him have opportunities to express his concerns and let me address them.
